The 10th Annual Desmond Tutu Peace Lecture will take place on Wednesday under the theme of Climate Change, in commemoration of Desmond Tutu's birthday. CEO of the Desmond and Leah Tutu Legacy Foundation, Piyushi Kotecha speaks on the event. Courtesy of #DStv403  CAPE TOWN - Archbishop Desmond Tutu is celebrating his 89th birthday on Wednesday. The annual Desmond Tutu Peace Lecture coincides with Tutu's birthday. This year it will be held under the theme 'Climate Justice Globally: Now and for the Future'. Ugandan climate change activist Vanessa Nakate (23) will be the guest speaker. She made global news when she was cropped out of a media photo taken in Davos.